First compute the slope \(m\).  Using the two points \((2,-11)\) and \((4,-25)\):

\[
m = \frac{-25 - (-11)}{4 - 2}
  = \frac{-25 + 11}{2}
  = \frac{-14}{2}
  = -7.
\]

So \(f(x)=mx+b=-7x+b\).  Plug in \(x=2,\;f(2)=-11\):

\[
-7\cdot2 + b = -11
\;\Longrightarrow\;
-14 + b = -11
\;\Longrightarrow\;
b = 3.
\]

Hence in slope–intercept form,

\[
\boxed{f(x) = -7x + 3.}
\]
